      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_InitialCheckForUpload",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to perform an initial check before an upload process. It retrieves the current billing period, checks the availability of linked servers, and provides information about the database server and database name. The procedure outputs four values: the current billing period, the server name, the database name, and a flag indicating whether all required linked servers are available."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving basic SQL operations such as executing another stored procedure, conditional logic, and simple SELECT statements. It does not involve complex joins, subqueries, or intricate business logic."
        }
      ]
    },
